# Cursor Rules for Rails Math Tutor Project

## Test Automation
- Automatically run tests when test files are saved
- Run specific test files when they are modified
- Run the full test suite on major changes

## Rails Best Practices
- Follow Rails conventions for file naming and structure
- Use proper Rails naming conventions for models, controllers, and views
- Implement proper RESTful routes and actions
- Use Rails helpers and form builders appropriately

## Code Quality
- Follow Ruby style guidelines (use RuboCop)
- Write descriptive test names and assertions
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Add appropriate comments for complex logic

## Testing Guidelines
- Write comprehensive tests for all models, controllers, and services
- Use fixtures or factories for test data
- Test both happy path and edge cases
- Ensure good test coverage

## File Organization
- Keep models focused on business logic
- Separate concerns in controllers
- Use service objects for complex operations
- Organize test files to mirror the app structure

## Security
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs
- Use strong parameters in controllers
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Follow Rails security best practices 